**Overall Meaning:**

This verse emphasizes the importance of understanding the divine presence woven into the very fabric of the world (śakvaryo lokeṣu protā). Those who grasp this knowledge become one with the world (lokī), experiencing a life of abundance and harmony. They are blessed with long life, abundant progeny, livestock, and great fame. They are in tune with the universal order and are never criticized because they embody the divine principle of unity and interconnectedness. 

The verse underscores the transformative power of knowledge, highlighting the ability to live in harmony with the world and achieve a life of prosperity and fulfillment. It emphasizes that this knowledge is a gift from the divine, leading to a life of understanding and interconnectedness. 
